<div class="app-container">
    <h1>Implementation Plan: Todo API & Master Plan DB Sync</h1>
    
    <div class="alert alert-info">
        <h3>📋 Strategic Context</h3>
        <p><strong>Problem</strong>: Text-based DailyPlan.tt and PriorityTodo.md require manual updates and AI assistance to stay current.</p>
        <p><strong>Solution</strong>: Migrate to application-driven workflow with REST API and database-driven Master Plan that auto-syncs.</p>
        <p><strong>Benefit</strong>: Reduces overhead, keeps Master Plan in sync automatically, enables IDE agents to create tasks directly without manual intervention.</p>
    </div>

    <hr style="margin: 30px 0;" />

    <h2>⚡ Current Status (Jan 14, 2026)</h2>
    
    <div class="alert alert-success">
        <h3>✅ PHASE 1A: Database & Schema (COMPLETE)</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>ApiToken Table Created</strong>:
                <ul>
                    <li>✅ <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/ApiToken.pm</code> – Result class with:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Hashed token storage (never plaintext in database)</li>
                            <li>Token expiration support (expires_at field)</li>
                            <li>Revocation tracking (revoked_at field)</li>
                            <li>Last used timestamp for auditing</li>
                            <li>Relationship to User table (user_id foreign key)</li>
                            <li>Optional token naming for user reference</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="alert alert-info" id="phase-1b-tokens">
        <h3>🟡 PHASE 1B: Token Usage Implementation (IN PROGRESS)</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Files Created</strong>:
                <ul>
                    <li>✅ <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/ApiToken.pm</code> – <a href="/Documentation/models/ApiToken.tt">Token schema</a> with hashed storage, expiration, revocation</li>
                    <li>✅ <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Controller/Api.pm</code> – <a href="/Documentation/controllers/Api.tt">Token management endpoints</a> (generate, list, revoke)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Files Modified</strong>:
                <ul>
                    <li>✅ <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Controller/Todo.pm</code> – <a href="/Documentation/controllers/Todo.tt#api-endpoints">Added REST API endpoints</a> + token validation (~380 lines)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>API Endpoints Implemented</strong>:
                <ul>
                    <li>✅ <code>POST /api/todo/create</code> – <a href="/api/doc/todo-create">Documentation</a> (Token auth required, dev-only)</li>
                    <li>✅ <code>GET /api/todo/{id}</code> – <a href="/api/doc/todo-get">Documentation</a> (Token auth required)</li>
                    <li>✅ <code>PUT /api/todo/{id}</code> – <a href="/api/doc/todo-update">Documentation</a> (Token auth required, partial update)</li>
                    <li>✅ <code>GET /api/project/{id}</code> – <a href="/api/doc/project-get">Documentation</a> (Token auth required)</li>
                    <li>✅ <code>POST /api/generate-token</code> – <a href="/api/doc/token-generate">Documentation</a> (Admin generates tokens)</li>
                    <li>✅ <code>GET /api/tokens</code> – <a href="/api/doc/tokens-list">Documentation</a> (List user tokens)</li>
                    <li>✅ <code>DELETE /api/tokens/{id}</code> – <a href="/api/doc/token-revoke">Documentation</a> (Revoke tokens)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Token Validation Implementation (IN PROGRESS)</strong>:
                <ul>
                    <li>✅ Created <code>ApiTokenValidator.pm</code> utility for consistent token validation – <a href="/Documentation/utils/ApiTokenValidator.tt">View Utility Docs</a></li>
                    <li>✅ Validate Bearer token in Authorization header</li>
                    <li>✅ Check token_hash against database (SHA-256 comparison)</li>
                    <li>✅ Verify token is active (is_active = 1)</li>
                    <li>✅ Check expiration (expires_at > NOW or NULL)</li>
                    <li>✅ Reject revoked tokens (revoked_at IS NULL check)</li>
                    <li>✅ Return clear error codes: 401 (invalid), 403 (revoked/expired), 400 (malformed)</li>
                    <li>✅ Update last_used_at timestamp on successful validation</li>
                    <li>✅ Applied validator to all /api/todo/* endpoints in <code>Todo.pm</code></li>
                    <li>📖 <strong>Documentation</strong>: Created <a href="/Documentation/ApiTokenReferenceGuide" target="_blank">ApiTokenReferenceGuide.tt</a> with usage instructions.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Schema Requirement (IMPORTANT)</strong>:
                <ul>
                    <li>Table <code>api_tokens</code> must exist in database before API endpoints can be used</li>
                    <li>Required columns: <code>id, user_id, token_hash, token_name, is_active, created_at, expires_at, last_used_at, revoked_at</code></li>
                    <li><strong>Admin Action</strong>: Create table via DBIx::Class migration or SQL directly</li>
                    <li>If table is missing: API requests will return 500 error + database error logged</li>
                    <li>Table schema defined in: <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/ApiToken.pm</code></li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Testing (READY)</strong>:
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Prerequisite</strong>: Ensure <code>api_tokens</code> table exists in database</li>
                    <li>Generate token via <code>POST /api/generate-token</code> (admin user, session auth)</li>
                    <li>Test token with endpoints:
                        <ul>
                            <li>POST /api/todo/create</li>
                            <li>GET /api/todo/:id</li>
                            <li>PUT /api/todo/:id</li>
                            <li>GET /api/project/:id</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Verify Bearer token header: <code>Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;</code></li>
                    <li>Check logs for token validation results</li>
                </ol>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="alert alert-warning" id="phase-2-schema-blocker">
        <h3>⚠️ BLOCKER: Phase 2 Schema Migration (Schema Comparison Bug)</h3>
        <p><strong>Issue</strong>: Schema comparison system fails to create <code>project_documentation_mapping</code> table from DBIx::Class Result definition.</p>
        <p><strong>Root Cause</strong>: Unknown – need to debug how the schema migration pipeline processes Result classes and generates DDL.</p>
        <p><strong>Blocking</strong>: Phase 2 (Master Plan refactoring) cannot proceed until this is resolved.</p>
        <p><strong>Task</strong>: Debug <code>deploy_schema.pl</code> and schema comparison logic to understand why new Result classes aren't recognized as "missing tables".</p>
    </div>

    <hr style="margin: 30px 0;" />

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    
    <p>Replace text-based task management with application-driven workflow using:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Todo/Project database tables as single source of truth</li>
        <li>REST API for programmatic todo creation from IDE/Zencoder agents</li>
        <li>Master Plan as database-driven query view (reads Projects/Todos, auto-syncs)</li>
        <li>Flagging mechanism in DailyPlan to bulk-create todos into application</li>
    </ul>

    <hr style="margin: 30px 0;" />

    <h2>Phase 1: REST API Endpoints (Dev-Only, comserv_server.pl) — ✅ COMPLETE</h2>
    
    <h3>How REST APIs Work</h3>
    
    <p><strong>Key Principle</strong>: REST APIs are <strong>endpoint-based</strong>. Each endpoint = one action. Add new endpoints as features are needed.</p>
    <p><strong>Example Growth Path</strong>:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Week 1</strong>: POST /api/todo/create, GET /api/todo/{id}, PUT /api/todo/{id}</li>
        <li><strong>Week 2</strong>: Need to delete todos? Add DELETE /api/todo/{id}</li>
        <li><strong>Week 3</strong>: Need project CRUD? Add POST /api/project/create, GET /api/project/{id}</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>No "master configuration"</strong>—just add controller methods with routes when needed. Simple and scalable.</p>

    <h3>1.1 Endpoint: POST /api/todo/create</h3>
    
    <p><strong>Purpose</strong>: Create todo from IDE/Zencoder agent without UI form</p>
    <p><strong>Authentication</strong>: Session-based (role check: admin/developer only)</p>
    <p><strong>Dev-Only Enforcement</strong>: Only accessible via comserv_server.pl (development). Blocked in Starman production environment.</p>
    
    <h4>Request Body (JSON)</h4>
    <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;"><code>{
  "subject": "string (required)",
  "description": "string (optional)",
  "project_id": "integer (optional, defaults to project 1)",
  "start_date": "YYYY-MM-DD (required)",
  "due_date": "YYYY-MM-DD (required)",
  "priority": "integer 1-10 (required, 1=Critical, 10=Optional)",
  "status": "integer 1-3 (required, 1=NEW, 2=IN_PROGRESS, 3=DONE)",
  "assigned_to": "string (optional, username)"
}</code></pre>
    
    <h4>Response (Success)</h4>
    <pre style="background: #e8f5e9; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;"><code>{
  "success": true,
  "todo_id": 42,
  "message": "Todo created successfully",
  "todo": { ... full todo record ... }
}</code></pre>
    
    <h4>Response (Error)</h4>
    <pre style="background: #ffebee; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;"><code>{
  "success": false,
  "error": "Missing required fields: subject, start_date",
  "code": "validation_error"
}</code></pre>

    <h3>1.2 Endpoint: GET /api/todo/{id}</h3>
    <p><strong>Purpose</strong>: Retrieve single todo for Master Plan or verification</p>
    <p><strong>Response</strong>: Full todo record (JSON)</p>

    <h3>1.3 Endpoint: PUT /api/todo/{id}</h3>
    <p><strong>Purpose</strong>: Update todo status/priority from IDE agent</p>
    <p><strong>Request Body</strong> (partial update allowed):</p>
    <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;"><code>{
  "status": "integer 1-3",
  "priority": "integer 1-10",
  "description": "string",
  "assigned_to": "string"
}</code></pre>

    <h3>1.4 Endpoint: GET /api/project/{id}</h3>
    <p><strong>Purpose</strong>: Retrieve project details for Master Plan query</p>
    <p><strong>Response</strong>: Project record with all fields</p>

    <h3>1.5 Token Management Endpoints</h3>
    <p><strong>POST /api/generate-token</strong> – Admin generates a token</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Request: <code>{ "token_name": "string (optional)", "expires_in_days": integer }</code></li>
        <li>Response: <code>{ "success": true, "token": "...", "warning": "Store securely" }</code></li>
        <li>Note: Token only returned once at creation</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>GET /api/tokens</strong> – List all user's tokens with metadata</p>
    <p><strong>DELETE /api/tokens/{id}</strong> – Revoke a token anytime</p>

    <hr style="margin: 30px 0;" />

    <h2 id="phase-2-master-plan">Phase 2: Master Plan as Database Query View + Documentation Mapping — 🔴 BLOCKED</h2>

    <h3>⚠️ DEBUGGING REQUIRED: Schema Comparison System</h3>
    
    <p><strong>Problem Statement</strong>:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Created <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/ProjectDocumentationMapping.pm</code> – Result class is complete and valid</li>
        <li>Ran <code>perl deploy_schema.pl</code> to deploy schema changes</li>
        <li>Result: Table NOT created in database. Schema comparison system doesn't recognize the new Result class.</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Debug Tasks</strong>:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Examine <code>deploy_schema.pl</code> – How does it discover Result classes?</li>
        <li>Check schema comparison logic – Why doesn't it detect missing <code>project_documentation_mapping</code> table?</li>
        <li>Verify DBIx::Class::Migration configuration – Is Result class properly registered?</li>
        <li>Test manual table creation – Confirm schema structure is correct once table exists</li>
        <li>Validate API integration – Ensure ProjectDocumentationMapping Result can be queried once table is created</li>
    </ol>

    <p><strong>Files to Investigate</strong>:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><code>Comserv/deploy_schema.pl</code> – Schema deployment entry point</li>
        <li><code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency.pm</code> – Schema definition and Result loading</li>
        <li><code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/</code> – All Result classes (check how new one fits pattern)</li>
        <li><code>.db/migrations/</code> – Check if migration files are being generated</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>2.1 Master Plan Structure (Query-Based)</h3>
    
    <p>Instead of hardcoded task lists, Master Plan will query database:</p>
    <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;"><code>[% projects = schema.resultset('Project').search({ status => { '!=' => 3 } } ) %]
[% FOREACH project IN projects %]
   &lt;h3&gt;[% project.name %] ([% project.project_code %])&lt;/h3&gt;
   
   [% doc_mappings = schema.resultset('ProjectDocumentationMapping').search({ project_id => project.id }) %]
   [% IF doc_mappings.count %]
      &lt;p&gt;Documentation:
      [% FOREACH mapping IN doc_mappings %]
         &lt;a href="/[% mapping.documentation_path %]"&gt;[% mapping.documentation_path %]&lt;/a&gt;
      [% END %]
      &lt;/p&gt;
   [% END %]
   
   [% todos = schema.resultset('Todo').search({ project_id => project.id, status => { '!=' => 3 } }) %]
   &lt;ul&gt;
   [% FOREACH todo IN todos %]
      &lt;li&gt;[% todo.subject %] (Priority: [% todo.priority %], Due: [% todo.due_date %])&lt;/li&gt;
   [% END %]
   &lt;/ul&gt;
[% END %]</code></pre>
    
    <p><strong>Benefit</strong>: Master Plan auto-updates as todos/projects change. No manual editing needed.</p>

    <h3>2.2 Create Linked Table: ProjectDocumentationMapping</h3>
    
    <p><strong>Design Rationale</strong>: Normalized table for flexibility (one project → multiple docs, one doc → multiple projects)</p>
    <p><strong>Table Structure</strong>:</p>
    <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;"><code>CREATE TABLE project_documentation_mapping (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    project_id INT NOT NULL,
    documentation_path VARCHAR(500) NOT NULL,  -- e.g., /Documentation/ConfigurationInfrastructure.tt#section-id
    is_primary TINYINT DEFAULT 0,              -- Flag primary doc for the project
    display_order INT,                         -- Order to display docs
    created_at DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (project_id) REFERENCES projects(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
);
</code></pre>
    <p><strong>Example Data</strong>:</p>
    <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;"><code>project_id=5, documentation_path=/Documentation/ConfigurationInfrastructure.tt#section-auth, is_primary=1
project_id=5, documentation_path=/Documentation/Troubleshooting.tt#section-config, is_primary=0
project_id=5, documentation_path=/Documentation/UserGuide.tt, is_primary=0
</code></pre>
    <p><strong>Benefit</strong>: One project can reference multiple docs. Master Plan knows exactly which docs describe each project.</p>

    <hr style="margin: 30px 0;" />

    <h2 id="phase-3-dailyplan-flagging">Phase 3: DailyPlan Flagging Mechanism</h2>
    
    <h3>3.1 Flag Format in DailyPlan.tt</h3>
    
    <p>Add <code>add_to_todo</code> attribute to tasks:</p>
    <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;"><code>&lt;div class="task-item" data-task-id="task-001" data-add_to_todo="true"&gt;
  &lt;h4&gt;Fix Todo Display Bug&lt;/h4&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Critical blocker for Daily Plans UI&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;button onclick="addTodoFromDailyPlan(this)" class="add-todo-btn"&gt;+ Add to Todo&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

    <h3>3.2 JavaScript Handler (New)</h3>
    
    <p>When user clicks "Add to Todo":</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Extract task details from DailyPlan DOM</li>
        <li>POST to <code>/api/todo/create</code> with mapped fields (requires Bearer token)</li>
        <li>On success: Mark task as "✅ Added to Todo", disable button</li>
        <li>Display todo_id in UI for tracking</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>3.3 PriorityTodo Integration</h3>
    
    <p>Similar mechanism for PriorityTodo.md:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>"Create Todo" button on each priority item</li>
        <li>Bulk action: "Create All Priority Todos at Once"</li>
        <li>Automatic mapping: PriorityTodo order → todo priority (1-10 scale)</li>
    </ul>

    <hr style="margin: 30px 0;" />

    <h2 id="phase-4-ide-agent">Phase 4: IDE Agent Integration — 🔵 PENDING (Phase 2)</h2>
    
    <h3>4.1 Zencoder Agent Workflow</h3>
    
    <p><strong>Old Workflow</strong>:</p>
    <pre>Agent → Manual text edit to DailyPlan.tt → Wait for review</pre>
    
    <p><strong>New Workflow</strong>:</p>
    <pre>Agent → POST /api/todo/create → Todo auto-added → Master Plan updates automatically</pre>

    <h3>4.2 API Call Example (Perl)</h3>
    <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;"><code>use LWP::UserAgent;
use JSON::MaybeXS;

my $ua = LWP::UserAgent->new;
my $url = 'http://localhost:3000/api/todo/create';

my $data = {
  subject => 'Implement user authentication',
  description => 'Add login/logout via Catalyst::Plugin::Authentication',
  project_id => 5,
  start_date => '2026-01-15',
  due_date => '2026-01-20',
  priority => 3,
  status => 1
};

my $response = $ua->post(
  $url,
  'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
  Content => encode_json($data)
);

if ($response->is_success) {
  my $result = decode_json($response->content);
  print "Todo created: " . $result->{todo_id} . "\n";
} else {
  warn "Error: " . $response->status_line;
}</code></pre>

    <hr style="margin: 30px 0;" />

